ga9P(){return"Registration and Access"},
ga9O(){return"Projects and Members"},
ga9M(){return"Calendar and View Modes"},
ga9N(){return"Managing Unavailability and Events"},
ga9H(){return"How do I sign up for the app?"},
ga9q(){return"You can sign up directly in the app using your email address. Alternatively, if another user invites you to join a project, you will receive an email with a registration link that guides you through account creation."},
ga9z(){return"I received an invitation email but I already have an account. What should I do?"},
ga9e(){return"If you are already registered and receive an invitation email, you do not need to do anything special: the system will automatically add you to the project as soon as the project owner uses your email address for the invite."},
ga9f(){return"You will still receive a notification to let you know that you have been added to the project."},
ga9y(){return"How can I create a new project?"},
ga9d(){return"From the main screen, select the option to create a new project. You will need to enter the project name (for example, the band name), and you can invite members afterward."},
ga9A(){return"How do I invite members to my project?"},
ga9g(){return'In project settings, open the "Members" or "Invite members" section. Enter the email addresses of the musicians you want to add.'},
ga9h(){return"The system will automatically send an invitation email to users who are not registered yet, while already registered members will receive a notification directly in the app."},
ga9B(){return"What happens if an invited member is not registered yet?"},
ga9i(){return"No problem. That person will receive an email with all registration instructions. Once registration is completed, they will be automatically added to the project that invited them."},
ga9G(){return'What is the difference between "Personal" and "Band" mode?'},
ga9o(){return"Personal mode: this is your personal agenda. Here you can add your unavailability (personal commitments, other projects, days when you cannot play). In this mode you only see your own commitments."},
ga9p(){return"Band mode: this is the group view. Here you can add band events (rehearsals and live shows) and see every member's unavailability, along with the scheduled events for the currently selected project."},
ga9x(){return"How can I change projects?"},
ga9c(){return"At the top of the calendar or from the main menu, you can select the project you want to view. Band mode always shows data for the currently selected project."},
ga9K(){return"Where do I add my unavailability?"},
ga9v(){return"Unavailability can only be added in Personal mode. These are personal commitments that apply to all projects you are part of."},
ga9J(){return"Where do I add rehearsals and live shows?"},
ga9u(){return"Rehearsals and live shows are added in Band mode, selecting the related project. These are events specific to that band."},
ga9I(){return"How does visibility of commitments work across different projects?"},
ga9r(){return"The system handles your global agenda in an intelligent way."},
ga9s(){return"When you add unavailability in Personal mode, it is automatically shared with all projects you belong to. Members of each band will see you as busy at that date and time."},
ga9t(){return"When you participate in an event (rehearsal or live show) with one band, you will still appear as busy in your other projects. This prevents other bands from scheduling conflicting rehearsals."},
ga9C(){return'What does "Maybe" status mean for an event?'},
ga9j(){return'"Maybe" status lets you mark an event (rehearsal or live show) as provisional or not yet confirmed. It is useful during planning when a date is being considered but not confirmed yet.'},
ga9k(){return"All members can see that the event is still being defined."},
ga9D(){return'Can I add unavailability as "Maybe"?'},
ga9l(){return'Yes. You can also use "Maybe" for unavailability, for example when you are not 100% sure about a commitment yet but want to signal a potential conflict to all your bands.'},
ga9F(){return'How are confirmed items visually different from "Maybe" items?'},
ga9n(){return'"Maybe" items are shown with a different visual style (for example lighter color, dashed style, or a dedicated icon) so their provisional nature is immediately clear compared to confirmed items.'},
ga9E(){return'Can I change an item from "Maybe" to confirmed?'},
ga9m(){return"Absolutely. You can edit an event or unavailability at any time and update its status as commitments become defined."},
